Job Description:
Responsibility:
 Participate in the company's network management, planning and implementation; (including firewall, VPN, intrusion detection, etc.) 
 Be responsible for the company's internal information security implementation, and maintenance, And Infrastructure setup 
 Be responsible for TW Office IT related requirement [Svr setup, Storage, Permission Settings, Backup&Restore etc.]
 End-user support  [HelpDesk; Others applications / Svr Room management /PABX, etc]

Candidate Qualification:
MUST HAVE
 Bachelor degree, Minimum 3+ Years of Work experience in same position;
 Familiar with the Windows / Linux operating system, and Permission/rights management; 
 Must have router/Firewall/Switch Configuration experiences. understanding the concept of network security and safety system and related safety equipment; 
 Know Virtualization platform with experience in operation and maintenance;
 Know popular Storage Devices and backup system with experience in operation and maintenance;
 Good at anti-virus sytem, vulnerability scanning, and understand of VPN, IDS, etc.;
 Rich experience in HelpDesk;
 Clear thinking, independent analysis and problem solving ability; 
 Good command in English;
 Have good learning, communication and team cooperation ability.

NICE TO HAVE
 Got Virtualization system setup / maintenance experiences is plus;
 EDA Tools support experiences is plus;
 PABX Maintenance experiences is plus;
